middleware package for @TARGET_TRIPLE@

Components:
- Redis @REDIS_VERSION@: @REDIS_STATUS@
- MinIO @MINIO_REF@
- etcd @ETCD_VERSION@
- patchelf @PATCHELF_VERSION@: @PATCHELF_STATUS@
- WinSW @WINSW_VERSION@: @WINSW_STATUS@

Toolchain inputs:
- Go @GO_VERSION@ for MinIO and etcd cross builds
- clang/LLVM package image for Redis Linux cross builds

Installed layout:
- bin/redis-server, bin/redis-cli, bin/redis-benchmark on Linux targets
- bin/redis-server.exe, bin/redis-cli.exe, bin/redis-benchmark.exe on MinGW workflow packages
- bin/minio
- bin/etcd, bin/etcdctl, bin/etcdutl
- bin/patchelf on Linux targets
- bin/winsw.exe and bin/winsw.xml on MinGW workflow packages
- conf/winsw.sample.xml on MinGW workflow packages
- Linux service helpers: install_redis_service.sh, uninstall_redis_service.sh,
  install_minio_service.sh, uninstall_minio_service.sh, and systemd templates
- Windows service helpers: install_redis_service.cmd, uninstall_redis_service.cmd,
  install_minio_service.cmd, uninstall_minio_service.cmd, and WinSW templates
- manifest.env

Service defaults:
- Redis is configured as a single-node service on 0.0.0.0:6379. The install
  script accepts service name, data directory, optional password, and service
  user.
- MinIO is configured as a single-node service on :9000 with console on :9001.
  The install script accepts service name, data directory, root user, root
  password, and service user on Linux.

Redis note:
MinGW workflow packages include Redis built with MSYS2, following the
redis-windows project build settings. Direct local build.sh MinGW builds stage
MinIO and etcd first; the workflow injects the MSYS2 Redis build before upload.

Utility note:
Linux packages include patchelf. MinGW workflow packages include WinSW built on
the Windows runner with the .NET/MSBuild toolchain before upload.
